Cape Town - The luxury home in Stellenbosch where three members of the Van Breda family were brutally murdered earlier this year, is for sale,&nbsp;Netwerk24&nbsp;reported on Thursday.All photos via RE/MAX.The house, in the De Zalze Winelands Golf Estate, is on the market for R6.2m.According to estate agents RE/MAX, the house boasts four bedrooms, four bathrooms, two living areas, a pool and two garages.RE/MAX s Deon de Swardt told Netwerk24 that a verbal offer had already been made on the property. An axe was used to kill owners of the property, Martin van Breda and his wife Teresa, and their 22-year-old son Rudi. The younger siblings, 16-year-old Marli and Henri, 20, survived the attack.Marli was left with a severed jugular and a severe head wound, while Henri was left with only scratches and bruises.Marli van Breda and her brother Henri are the main beneficiaries of an estate valued at about R200m.It has been said that it is unlikely that Marli will remember the incident. Marli and Henri have not seen each other since the attack.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.